# PineScript v6 Validation

When generating or editing PineScript, always validate against these rules before presenting code.

## Mandatory Structure

- First line: `//@version=6`
- Exactly one declaration: `indicator("Title")`, `strategy("Title")`, or `library("Title")`

## Never Use (Deprecated in v6)

- `security()` -> `request.security()`
- `study()` -> `indicator()`
- `transp=` -> `color.new(color, 0-100)`
- `iff()` -> ternary `condition ? a : b`
- `tostring()` -> `str.tostring()`
- `tonumber()` -> `str.tonumber()`
- `input.integer()` -> `input.int()`
- `input.resolution()` -> `input.timeframe()`

## Does NOT Exist (LLMs hallucinate these)

- `plot.style_dashed` — use `plot.style_line` with `linewidth`
- `plot.style_dotted` — use `plot.style_circles`

## Type Casting

```pinescript
// WRONG
bool x = na
int y = na

// CORRECT
bool x = bool(na)
int y = int(na)
```

## Common Traps

- `fill()` args must be same type — cannot mix `hline` and `plot`
- `input.int()` / `input.float()` use `defval=`, NOT `def=`
- `request.security()` without `lookahead=barmerge.lookahead_off` repaints

## Limits

- Max 64 plot calls (`plot`, `plotshape`, `hline`, `fill`, `bgcolor`, `barcolor`)
- Max 40 `request.*` calls
- ~70K compiled character limit
